  "texts": [
    "Token-level attacks use discrete optimization to create adversarial suffixes and bypass safety guardrails through gradient-guided token replacements (Zou et al., 2023).",
    "Prompt-level attacks employ automated semantic manipulations to generate human understandable jailbreak prompts (Chao et al., 2023).",
    "A key challenge for existing attack methods is efficiently selecting the optimal attack strategy while minimizing the instability arising from the inherent randomness in LLM generation.",
    "On the other hand, researchers have proposed various defenses to deal with these attacks.",
    "Prompt-level defenses check input prompts for malicious content before model generation (Robey et al., 2023), while model-level defenses fine-tune LLMs to implement safe response (Dai et al., 2023)."
